WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.000
So I'll update everybody regarding the Echelon 3 data for specifically for diffuse large B-cell

00:00:05.000 --> 00:00:12.540
lymphoma. I think this doesn't require an introduction per se. This is the landscape of

00:00:12.540 --> 00:00:19.500
targeted therapies available now, and on the far right is the most recent one FDA approved and is

00:00:19.500 --> 00:00:25.860
on the NCCA guidelines based on the Echelon 3 trial. This is for patients with relapsed refractory

00:00:25.860 --> 00:00:32.600
diffuse large B-cell lymphoma after two prior lines of therapy. They should not have received

00:00:32.600 --> 00:00:39.240
any lanolamide-based therapy or burntuximab or dotin. They technically were either progression

00:00:39.240 --> 00:00:44.780
after transplant or CAR or were ineligible for either of these. Had to have good performance

00:00:44.780 --> 00:00:51.220
status, measurable disease, and excluded CNS disease. The total number of patients on this

00:00:51.220 --> 00:00:55.840
study was 230. They were randomized to the experimental arm, which is burntuximab or dotin,

00:00:55.860 --> 00:01:01.560
at a dose of 1.2 milligrams per kilo every three weeks, plus rituxan and lanolamide. The lanolamide

00:01:01.560 --> 00:01:09.780
dosing was 20 milligrams. The standard arm was placebo plus rituxan plus lanolamide at the same

00:01:09.780 --> 00:01:16.400
doses. There was stratification based on CD30 status, cell of origin, prior CAR-T-cell therapy,

00:01:16.520 --> 00:01:21.120
and prior transplant. And the primary endpoint here was overall survival in the intentivity

00:01:21.120 --> 00:01:25.320
population, as well as the other endpoints noted on the slide there.

00:01:25.860 --> 00:01:30.020
This data have already been presented. So just to summarize, first of all, in terms of the

00:01:30.020 --> 00:01:36.480
treatment, the median number of prior therapies on this study was three, with 70% of patients having

00:01:36.480 --> 00:01:44.100
stage three or four disease, 60% of patients had IPIs three or higher, and 20, sorry, 30% of

00:01:44.100 --> 00:01:49.880
patients had prior CAR-T, and 20% of the patients had prior Bispecific. So reasonably

00:01:49.880 --> 00:01:55.040
heavily pre-treated patient population. And here you can see the response rates on the left-hand

00:01:55.040 --> 00:01:55.360
side.

00:01:55.860 --> 00:02:02.500
64% overall response rates with 40% CRs in comparison to the lanolamide rituxan experimental

00:02:02.500 --> 00:02:08.320
arm. And there isn't really a trend, just to suffice it to say, whether there were CD30

00:02:08.320 --> 00:02:15.000
negative by less than 1% or positive, there is indeed a response there. And I'll come back to

00:02:15.000 --> 00:02:20.520
this in just a little bit. In terms of the progression-free survival and overall survival

00:02:20.520 --> 00:02:25.620
curve, you can see here, respectively on the left and on the right-hand side, there is an

00:02:25.860 --> 00:02:31.620
improvement in progression-free survival and improvement in overall survival in favor of the

00:02:31.620 --> 00:02:36.800
brentuximab-based strategy in this third line setting. And this data is what has led to the

00:02:36.800 --> 00:02:41.740
inclusion of the regimen in the NCCN guidelines and its availability for our patients. It's a

00:02:41.740 --> 00:02:47.840
reasonably well-tolerated regimen of therapy. There is certainly with the addition of an extra

00:02:47.840 --> 00:02:52.480
agent, there is increased toxicity in terms of cytopenia. So there's more neutropenia,

00:02:52.580 --> 00:02:55.500
thrombocytopenia, and anemia. There is certainly more,

00:02:55.860 --> 00:03:07.360
brentuximab-related neurotoxicity at 20% all grade and 4% grade 3 or 4. This was a dose-reduced

00:03:07.360 --> 00:03:12.160
regimen, so at least that mitigates some of the neurotoxicity, but really nothing beyond that

00:03:12.160 --> 00:03:19.380
that stood out. In regards to what was updated this year at ASH was really this data regarding

00:03:19.380 --> 00:03:25.840
CD30 expression. And just to summarize this quickly is that really CD30 expression is not,

00:03:25.860 --> 00:03:32.700
visible CD30 expression by immunohistochemistry is not required for response. So you can see

00:03:32.700 --> 00:03:39.100
on the left-hand side there, the overall response rate in the lenalidomide, sorry, in the BV lenalidomide

00:03:39.100 --> 00:03:45.220
group, and then looking at with or without any significant expression, there's not a substantial

00:03:45.220 --> 00:03:50.160
difference. And that just, this highlights really, first of all, for those of you who are familiar

00:03:50.160 --> 00:03:55.820
with the studies that are done with brentuximab and dotin in CD30 positive disease, we did,

00:03:55.860 --> 00:04:04.020
this in peripheral T-cell lymphoma, in lymphomotor papulosis, which is universally CD30 positive.

00:04:04.020 --> 00:04:12.680
And in other studies, our method of detection for CD30 expression is immunohistochemistry,

00:04:12.680 --> 00:04:18.620
and that's a visible technique. So that's clearly, as you can see, both here and in

00:04:18.620 --> 00:04:25.080
many other studies, that visible IHC-based strategy is not adequate for assessment of

00:04:25.080 --> 00:04:25.860
target.

00:04:25.860 --> 00:04:32.480
Whereas here, even in the absence of a visible CD30 expression, there's actually clear responses

00:04:32.480 --> 00:04:38.140
with clear benefit there. And this is also more broadly not limited to CD30. The same

00:04:38.140 --> 00:04:45.040
thing happens when we do immunohistochemistry for assessment of CD19, CD20, CD22. Those

00:04:45.040 --> 00:04:51.860
techniques are limited, perhaps at least in CD19 and 20. You have a little bit of a more

00:04:51.860 --> 00:04:55.360
sensitive technique by flow cytometry, so you can enhance the technique.

00:04:55.360 --> 00:04:55.860
But again, it's a little bit more specific, but it's a little bit more sensitive technique by flow cytometry, so you can enhance the technique. But again,

00:04:55.860 --> 00:05:01.620
highlights the broader point that our IHC techniques are not adequate for detection of the target that

00:05:01.620 --> 00:05:11.060
we are going after. And to summarize this data in terms of, again, this impact of CD30, visible CD30

00:05:11.060 --> 00:05:18.180
expression here, really across the board, there seems to be a benefit in some of these categories,

00:05:18.180 --> 00:05:22.420
like progression-free survival and overall survival. There's actually a statistically

00:05:22.420 --> 00:05:23.860
significant hazard ratio there. So really establish that there's a significant impact on CD30 expression.

00:05:23.860 --> 00:05:24.180
So really establish that there's a significant hazard ratio there. So really establish that there's a significant hazard ratio there.

00:05:24.180 --> 00:05:24.660
So really establish that there's a significant hazard ratio there. So really establish that there's a significant hazard ratio there.

00:05:24.660 --> 00:05:25.140
So really establish that there's a significant hazard ratio there. So really establish that there's a significant hazard ratio there.

00:05:25.140 --> 00:05:30.500
really establishes the availability of this regimen. And this is indeed on the updated NCCN

00:05:30.500 --> 00:05:36.660
guidelines as third line and beyond another strategy. The duration of remissions with this,

00:05:36.660 --> 00:05:41.700
the duration of responses with this strategy is relatively short. So certainly as a palliative

00:05:41.700 --> 00:05:47.300
strategy or perhaps the patients that are needed bridging to an allotransplant or other subsequent

00:05:47.300 --> 00:05:52.580
lines of therapy, it's perhaps some utility there. So I'll stop there. Thank you.

00:05:55.140 --> 00:05:55.900
Okay.
